The location, for me, is ideal, the reception very friendly and efficient and the rooms great value for the price.	This is not a five star hotel but you are not paying five star prices and as stated above the location is awesome.	This is an enjoyable way to reach the city, but gets expensive if there is a group of you as it costs $2.50 each way.	Parking was an extra charge, but cheaper than downtown, and unless you're staying in the burbs, parking is going to cost you.	I stay at other expensive hotels similar to this and they do this service, they also do not charge for the bikes if you are a guest of the hotel.